Mr. Bruno Bayet, Chief Finance Officer, Lafarge Africa Plc  has resigned his appointment, the company announced on Wednesday. In a letter sent to the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), Mr. Mobolaji Balogun, the company’s Chairman, commended Bruno for his personal commitment, dedication and the significant contributions made during his three years at Lafarge Africa.
Balogun said that the company had initiated the process of finding a new Chief Finance Officer and would be considering internal and external candidates. Marie-Christiane Kaul-Meledge has been appointed as the interim Chief Finance Officer of Lafarge Africa, succeeding Bayet emerged the company’s Chief Financial Officer on October 1, 2016 following the resignation of Mr. Anders Kristiansson on September 30, 2016.